This document describes the execution environment and the directory
configuration of the OZ++ system.

o Execution Environment

The OZ++ system should be executed in the following environment:

  - SunOS 4.1.3, or 4.1.4
    whose kernel has been reconfigured to use shared memory, required.
  - Disk space of 60MB for make and 60MB for installation, required.
  - Swap space of 40MB required at the time of exceution.
  - Sparc Station 2, or faster desired.


o Necessary Tools

The following tools are required to use the demo system of OZ++:

  - X Window System (Release 5 or later is desirable)
  - Tcl(7.3)/Tk(3.6)
     (jp-patch, add-input3.6, and TkPixmap3.6 are required.)
     This can be ftp'd from ftp.aud.alcatel.com:/tcl.
  - gcc 2.7.0
  - perl 4.* or 5.*
  - gzip

